<HEADLINE> Italy Beats Netherlands in Penalty Shootout </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Italy defeated the Netherlands 3-
1 in a penalty shootout on Thursday to meet France in the final of
the European championship following the teams ended up 0-0 after
extra time.
</P>
<P>
The Italians reached Sunday's final in Rotterdam for the first
time since 1968.
</P>
<P>
Frank de Boer missed from the spot for the second time in the
match and the Dutch missed four in a row, two in normal time.
</P>
