<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Karachi Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Karachi Stock Exchange
Thursday finished the day 0.79 percent down, losing 12.22 points
to 1528.91 points on a record thin volume of 92 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Out of a total of 223 active companies, 53 posted gains, 117
suffered losses and 53 remained unchanged while the market capital
moved from 398.94 billion rupees (7.53 billion U.S.dollars) on
Wednesday to 396.157 billion rupees (7.47 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
Only 92.23 million shares changed hand Thursday compared with
101.609 million shares traded on the previous day which emerged to
be the second lowest turnover in the last couple of months.
</P>
</TEXT>
