<HEADLINE> Netherlands and Italy Play Goalless at halftime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Frank de Boer missed a penalty five minutes after Gianluca
Zambrotta had been ejected .
</P>
<P>
The Italian midfielder was sent off in the 33th minute for two
yellow cards.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch should have taken a halftime lead when Patrick
Kluivert was fouled inside the area but De Boer's penalty kick was
saved by goalkeeper Francesco Toldo.
</P>
<P>
The winner plays France, who beat Portugal 2-1 in Wednesday's
semifinal, in Sunday's final in Rotterdam, the Netherlands.
</P>
