<HEADLINE> Dramatized "Souls of Red Crag" Exhibition Welcomed in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- "Souls of Red Crag", a dramatized
exhibition in memory of revolutionary martyrs during the civil war
period (1945-1949) received thundering applause from a Beijing
audience this evening.
</P>
<P>
"Souls of Red Crag" was presented by actors from Chongqing
Municipality in west China. It tells how members of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) and their followers fought against the
Kuomintang rulers right before New China was founded in 1949. The
performance was attended by Chinese Vice Premier Li Lanqing and
Ding Guangen, head of the Publicity Department of CPC Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
At the close of the show, Li and other officials went onstage
to shake hands with the actors, who are all workers from the
Chongqing Geleshan Revolutionary Memorial Hall.
</P>
<P>
The officials congratulated the actors' on their accurate
interpretation of the communist fighters' heroic deeds in a
Kuomintang detention center at Red Crag in Chongqing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
