<HEADLINE> Mercosur 18th Summit Starts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
De la Rua called in his inaugural speech for the gradual
incorporation of Chile and Bolivia as full members of Mercosur,
which is made up of Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay, and Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
The agreements arrived at by the foreign and economy ministers
in the preparatory meeting held Thursday in Buenos Aires will be
submitted during the summit to the approval of the presidents.
</P>
<P>
The summit being held at the Palace of San Martin is attended
by the presidents De la Rua, Fernando Henrique Cardoso, of Brazil;
Luis Gonzalez, of Paraguay, and Jorge Batlle, of Uruguay, as well
as Ricardo Lagos, of Chile. The president of Bolivia, Hugo Banzer,
will be absent.
</P>
<P>
This is one of the ordinary summits that are held every six
months. Argentina is occupying during the first semester of this
year the pro tempore presidency of the bloc.
</P>
<P>
The proposal of the joint parliamentary commission that
sessioned Thursday in the Argentine City of Santa Fe for the
conformation of Mercosur into a common market will also be
examined.  
