<HEADLINE> Chirac Meets With Armenian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 30 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac met
with visiting Armenian President Robert Kocharian on Friday and
discussed with the latter bilateral relations and the situation in
Upper Karabakh.
</P>
<P>
Chirac said after the meeting that the relations between France
and Armenia are very important and close because of the big
Armenian community in France.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his sympathy with Armenian nation's tragic
exodus in 1915, during which hundreds of thousands of Armenians
died.
</P>
<P>
As for the 10-year-old conflict in Upper Karabakh between
Armenia and Azerbaijan, Chirac said that both sides of the
conflict are more and more aware of the need to find a political
solution.
</P>
<P>
With Russia and the United States, France is one of the three
co-presidents of the Group of Minsk in charge of mediating the
conflict in Upper Karabakh.
</P>
<P>
The French president also expressed his support to the recent
vote by parliament assembly of the Strasbourg-based Council of
Europe to admit Armenia as a member country.
</P>
<P>
Kocharian said that he expects a lot from his direct talks with
Azerbaijani President Heydar Aliyev, which are aimed at finding a
positive and lasting solution to the conflict in Upper Karabakh.
</P>
