<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets German Chancellor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji and
German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder met here Friday and reached
broad consensus on bilateral relations and international issues of
mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
Schroeder extended warm welcome to Zhu and highly valued the
current bilateral relations. He said the German-Sino relation is"
very good," and proceeding smoothly in all aspects.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation in the fields of economy, trade, science and
technology, culture, education, environmental protection, and
legal dialogue has reached new level, he noted.
</P>
<P>
He said Germany supports China's early entry into the World
Trade Organization and the German businessmen are fully confident
in the expansion of investment and cooperation in China.
</P>
<P>
He said the German government attaches great importance to
China's positive role in world affairs, and Germany will continue
to pursue the One-China policy.
</P>
<P>
Zhu appreciated Schroeder's positive remarks on bilateral
relations. He said, since Schroeder's visit to China last year,
the two countries have made major headway in their cooperation in
various fields. The close political contacts and consultations,
the steadily-increasing trade, and major projects of cooperation
achieved recently, will have far-reaching impact on bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Zhu pointed out the German government is upholding its One
China policy and keeping its promise in earnest. " We highly
appreciate it," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier said both China and Germany are important
countries in the world.
</P>
<P>
China values the status and influence of Germany in Europe and
the world at large, is willing to develop steady and all-round
cooperation with Germany on the basis of mutual respect, equality
and mutual benefit, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said, his current visit aims at pushing the bilateral
relations to a new high. China and Germany share common or similar
points of views, their economies are highly complementary, and
have already established wide cooperation with solid foundation.
The further development of bilateral relations has huge potential
and broad prospective.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders noted that the two countries enjoy trust-worthy
partnership. They pledged to make utmost efforts to further
promote bilateral cooperation in the new century, enhance
bilateral cooperations in high technology, environment protection,
and between small and medium size enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Schroeder highly praised China's achievements since adopting
the policy of opening up and reform. He said, Germany is willing
to participate in China's modernization drive, including the large-
scale development in China' west. He also briefed Zhu on the
European integration.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier said that China hopes the European
integration will not only be conducive to peace, stability and
prosperity in Europe, but also will benefit world peace,
development,multi-polarization. He hoped that the European Union
will undertake exchanges and cooperation with other regions and
countries on the basis of equality and mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
After their meeting, the two leaders also attended the signing
ceremony on six cooperation agreements, concerning industry and
technology, legality,petro-chemical complex in Nanjing and the
construction of a demonstration project of high-speed magnet-
suspension train in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Also on Friday, the Chinese premier met here with German
Federal Assembly President Wolfgang Thierse. Thierse said the
Chinese premier's current visit would bring bilateral ties to an
all-round development.
</P>
<P>
Thierse added the German federal assembly is willing to
contribute its efforts to further developing bilateral friendly
ties.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier, who arrived here on Thursday for an
official visit to Germany, said he hoped the legislature in both
China and Germany would strengthen their exchanges and cooperation,
increase mutual understanding and expand common consensus.
</P>
<P>
Zhu also briefed the German parliament leader on the Chinese
government's policy on Taiwan issue and national reunification.
</P>
<P>
Thierse said the German federal assembly supports the German
government's position of upholding One-China policy and hopes
China will achieve its reunification as early as possible.
</P>
<P>
Germany is the second leg of the Chinese premier's tour of six
European nations and the European Union headquarters. He has
visited Bulgaria and will travel on to Luxembourg, the Netherlands,
Italy and Belgium. 
</P>
</TEXT>
