<HEADLINE> British Firm to Take Part in China's Pension Reforms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Standard Life Assurance Co.
of Britain will participate in the reforms of the Chinese pension
system.
</P>
<P>
Officials at the Ministry of Labor and Social Security of China
have signed an agreement with the British government, welcoming
Standard Life Assurance Co. and other British insurance firms to
take part in the reforms, said an official of the company's
Shanghai branch.
</P>
<P>
The Standard Life Assurance Co. will send its best experts to
provide technical training and consulting services to China, said
Robert Knight, who is in charge of the Asia-Pacific affairs of the
company, during a visit to China recently.
</P>
<P>
China's aging population has become a problem, experts said. By
the year 2025, one in three Shanghai residents will be elderly.
</P>
<P>
The country is seeking solutions to maintain the standard of
living of the retirees. 
</P>
