<HEADLINE> China Builds New Bridge in Eastern Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The bridge helps ease traffic jams in the northern part of the
province and will promote economic development in Nanchang,
Jiujiang, Jingdezhen cities as well as the lower reaches of the
Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
It took China two and a half years to build the cable bridge
spanning Jiujiang and Jingdezhen. The bridge crosses Poyang Lake,
China's largest freshwater lake.
</P>
