<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Builds World's Biggest Goose Liver Production Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIHAI, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The world's biggest production base
of goose livers will be built in Hepu County in southwest China's
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region within four years.
</P>
<P>
After the base is built, the annual goose liver production
capacity will be one million kilograms, with annual output of 25
million yuan (about three million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Hongyan Foodstuff Co. Ltd and Hepu County Canned Food
Factory will invest 10 million yuan (about 1.2 million US dollars)
in the project.
</P>
<P>
The goose liver is a popular food in Europe and the United
States, and the world market's annual demand stands at over 10
million kilograms.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi is one of the main breeding areas of geese, and a cross-
bred goose in the city of Beihai is famous for its flavor.
</P>
</TEXT>
