<HEADLINE> China to Publish Ten Key Academic Books </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Social
Sciences (CASS) plans to publish ten important academic books in
the coming five years, including the proposed 210-volume History
of Various Countries.
</P>
<P>
The other nine books are Selected Works of CASS Scholars,
History of Western Aesthetics, Textual Research on History of
Chinese Legal System, Chinese Archaeology, Dictionary of
Historical Place Names, History of World Civilization,
Vicissitudes in Modern Chinese Society, History of Chinese
Kuomintang from 1894 to 1949, and History of Shang Dynasty (B.C.
16 c - 11 c).
</P>
<P>
The China Social Sciences Publishing House and China Social
Sciences Documentation Publishing House will produce the acclaimed
scholarly works.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the two CASS publishing houses said that all the
works reflect the latest academic achievements made by well-known
Chinese social scientists.
</P>
<P>
As a government think tank in China, the CASS annually
publishes a number of outstanding books, which are also important
research materials for overseas experts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
