<TEXT>

<P>
MANILA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph
Estrada and visiting Spanish Prime Minister Jose Maria Aznar
pledged Friday to further reinforce bilateral relations between
their two countries.
</P>
<P>
During their joint press conference in the Presidential Palace,
the two leaders underscored the need to heighten economic
relations between their countries, particularly through increased
trade and investments.
</P>
<P>
