investments in the Philippines as he noted that the signing of the
Philippines-Spain General Treaty of Friendship and Cooperation
would lead to stronger ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
"It symbolizes, without any doubt, the decision and resolve of
our countries to begin a new road together. In brief, Spain and
the Philippines look ahead towards the future together," Aznar
said.
</P>
<P>
The visiting Spanish leader arrived in Manila Thursday evening
for a three-day official visit. Aznar is expected to conclude his
visit here Saturday evening and leave for Bahrain. 
</P>
