<HEADLINE> Death Toll of China Boat Tragedy Climbs to 121 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The death toll of the boat tragedy
which occurred on China's largest river of Yangtze June 22 has
risen to 121 with eight more bodies recovered today.
</P>
<P>
The search and rescue operation has entered the 9th straight
day, said an official from the county of Hejiang, the site of the
accident in southwest China's Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
Insurance companies have paid 516,000 yuan (about 52,169 U.S.
dollars) in compensation. And grief-relief funds totaling 258,000
yuan (about 31,084 U.S. dollars) have also been provided to
relatives of the victims.
</P>
<P>
The passenger vessel Rong Jian, which was designed to carry a
maximum of 101 people, had 221 passengers on board when it hit a
rock and sank while sailing in foggy conditions on June 22.
</P>
