<HEADLINE> Tian Congming Appointed as Xinhua News Agency President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Tian Congming, former director of
the State Administration of Radio, Film and Television, today
assumed the post of president of Xinhua News Agency, following
former president Guo Chaoren who died of illness June 15.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Nan Zhenzhong was named editor-in-chief of the state-
run news agency.
</P>
<P>
Tian, born in 1943, graduated from Beijing Normal University in
1970 and was assigned to work in the Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region. He worked as a correspondent at Xinhua's Inner Mongolia
Bureau from 1974 to 1980.
</P>
<P>
He became a member of the Standing Committee of and secretary-
general of the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Regional Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) in 1983, deputy secretary of the
CPC Inner Mongolia Autonomous Regional Committee in 1984, deputy
secretary of the CPC Tibet Autonomous Regional Committee in 1988,
vice-minister of Radio, Film and Television in 1990, and director
of the State Administration of Radio, Film and Television in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Nan Zhenzhong, born in 1942, graduated from Zhengzhou
University in 1964 and started to work at Xinhua the same year.
</P>
<P>
He served as deputy director and director of Xinhua's Shandong
Bureau. Nan was appointed as the agency's deputy editor-in-chief
in 1985 and vice-president of Xinhua in 1993.
</P>
<P>
He was also elected vice-president of All-China Journalists
Association in 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
