<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Take Census of Foreign Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania is conducting a
survey on foreign investors in the country in a bid to create a
reliable database for external capital inflows and outflows, local
newspapers reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Director of Economic Policy of the Bank of Tanzania Peter Noni
told the media Thursday that based on the survey results,
information on balance of payments would be improved.
</P>
<P>
"This will enhance macro-economic policy formulation with a
view to promoting better investment policies," he said.
</P>
<P>
Noni said the survey, which commenced on June 12, was expected
to last until the end of July when all questionnaires distributed
to companies would have been returned for processing and analysis.
</P>
<P>
He urged all those concerned to finish the required data as the
 information gathered would be confidential and be used for
intended purposes only.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,500 investors have been identified for the survey
so far in Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
The survey is being conducted by the Bank of Tanzania in
collaboration with Tanzania Investment Center and National Bureau
of Statistics. 
