<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice Premier Li Lanqing
wants to see improvements made to the country's art education
programs so that they can better serve social and economic
development.
</P>
<P>
Li made an inspection tour yesterday to a number of art
institutes in Beijing, including the Chinese Opera Institute, the
Beijing Institute of Dance and the Beijing Film Academy.
</P>
<P>
The reform on art education will focus on better training of
qualified people to meet the requirement of local and national
development in the 21st century, Li said at a meeting after his
