<HEADLINE> Beijing Reception Marks Sino-Thai Diplomatic Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People's Association
for Friendship with Foreign Countries (CPAFFC) held a reception
here this evening, marking the 25th anniversary of the
establishment of Sino-Thai diplomatic relations.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zhenghua, vice chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress (NPC), and former Thai Prime Minister
Anand Panyarachun attended the reception.
</P>
<P>
CPAFFC President Qi Huaiyuan said on the occasion that the two
countries are good neighbors, and their peoples have a time-
honored friendship, adding that they have trusted each other since
the establishment of diplomatic relations, and had cooperation in
political, economic, cultural and other areas.
</P>
<P>
Sino-Thai relations have set a fine example for developing good-
neighborliness and mutually beneficial cooperation between
countries with different social systems, he said, expressing the
belief that such relations will achieve even greater success in
the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Anand, who serves as a special envoy of the Thai government,
told the gathering that bilateral relations have gone well since
the forging of diplomatic relations 25 years ago, and the two
countries have taken into consideration their shared interests,
and had fruitful cooperation in various fields.
</P>
<P>
He said that growing trade ties and mutual investment will
instill new vigor to the further development of Sino-Thai
relations. Anand also spoke highly of China's constructive role
and responsible attitude in the international arena. 
</P>
