<HEADLINE> 7 Dead, Dozens Ill After Eating Poisonous Fish in Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Phnom Penh, June 30 (Xinhua) -- At least seven people were
confirmed dead and some 70 others fell ill after eating poisonous
fish in Cambodia's northern province of Siem Reap from June 23 to
27, police said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The fish the victims ate were known as Kampot fish. They were
caught from Sreng Stream, about 60 km to the northwest of the
provincial town.
</P>
<P>
Ou Em, penal police chief in the province, said the fish,
believed to be poisonous, will be sent for medial examination to
Phnom Penh next week.
</P>
<P>
The police said it is the first time that villagers died or
fell ill after eating the fish. 
</P>
</TEXT>
