<HEADLINE> Angolan Government Troops Retake Strategic Rebel Bastions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan Armed Forces (FAA) has
conquered a strategic bastion of the rebels in the central Bie
Province, giving a strong punch to the rebels led by Jonas
Savimbi, the official newspaper Jornal de Angola reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Located between Kuito, capital city of the Bie Province, and
Luena, capital of the Moxico Province, the municipality of Cuemba
is a strategic point for the rebels, especially after they lost
the political and military headquarters of Bailundo and Andulo
last September and October.
</P>
<P>
The city is important for the rebels because it is the place
where the rebels organize guerrilla groups and launch scattered
attacks around the country, said the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Besides the crushing defeat in this area, which has been under
the control of the rebels for 12 years, the rebels also suffered
heavy casualties in the neighboring town of Munhango, said the
newspaper without mentioning the exact number.
</P>
<P>
After the defeat in the two districts in the Bie Province, the
rebels fled to the north and the south of the area.
</P>
<P>
"We've started the clean-up operation along the railway from
Munhango to Cuemba," said the chief of the general staff of the
fifth brigade of the motorized infantry, adding that the rebels
showed their resistance, but were repelled by the government
troops.
</P>
<P>
During the recent battles in the eastern Bie Province, many
Savimbi's soldiers surrendered to the government troops. "It is
due to the pessimistic conditions of the rebels," said the
official newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Munhango and Cuemba, located in the Angolan central highland,
are adjacent to Angola's eastern provinces Moxico and Lunda-sul,
where the rebels have their traditional bastions, said local
analysts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
