<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria listed Among Poorest Countries by UNDP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria was among the 24 poorest
countries in the world, according to 2000 Human Development Report
(HDR), published by the United Nations Development Programme
(UNDP) in New York recently.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria was placed the 151st, out of a total of 174 countries
and regions in the world, a leading Nigerian newspaper Friday
quoted the report as saying.
</P>
<P>
"As if pointing to Nigeria, the report dwelt extensively on the
failure of developing countries to make positive impact on their
citizens despite moving from military dictatorship to democracy,"
said the Guardian concerning the UNDP's report.
</P>
<P>
But the Nigerian office of the UNDP, at the same time, said in
its own report that the country had no business being poor if
only all its abundant natural resources were properly harnessed.
</P>
</TEXT>
