<BODY>
<HEADLINE> No Over-age Players in South Africa's Olympic Squad in Sydney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 30 (Xinhua) -- South African soccer
authority has decided not to send any over-age players to the
Olympic Games soccer tournament in September.
</P>
<P>
Officials said on Friday that the under-23 coach Ephraim
Mashaba will bring to Sydney the same team that qualified for the
16-team event.
</P>
<P>
International Olympic Committee rules allow a team to field
three over-age players in the finals, but all qualifying matches
are played at under-23 level.
</P>
<P>
Mashaba said, "This is an honor for the boys for doing such an
excellent job in the qualifiers," said Mashaba.
</P>
<P>
South Africa have been drawn in the same group as Brazil, Japan
and Slovakia at the Olympics. 
</P>
