<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Finish Week Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks fell 131.02
points, or 0.80 percent, to finish the week at 16,155.78, due to
the slump of the European telecom shares.
</P>
<P>
The turnover went down to 8.163 billion HK dollars (1.046
billion U.S. dollars) from the 11.178 billion HK dollars (1.433
billion U.S. dollars) Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The market rebounded slightly in the afternoon trading as the
government's decision to give up its public housing plan relieved
the property stocks.
</P>
<P>
Two new listings, Phoenix Satellite Television and Excel
Technology International, had a disappointing performance and
closed almost at the level of the issue prices.
</P>
<P>
Of the four sub-indices, Finance, Utilities and Properties
gained 1.73 percent, 1.06 percent and 1.48 percent, respectively,
while Commerce and Industry lost 2.68 percent.
</P>
<P>
China-related stocks ended slightly lower with the Hang Seng
China Enterprises Index down 0.40 percent and the Hang Seng China-
Affiliated Corp Index down 0.03 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng IT Index and the Hang Seng IT Portfolio Index
also declined by 3.70 percent and 2.02 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The blue chips opened up 240.83 points Monday and registered
gains on the first three trading days, before declining Thursday
and Friday. Compared to the last week, the Hang Seng Index rose
417.70 points, or 2.65 percent, this week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
