<HEADLINE> 29 Killed, 200 Injured In Fireworks Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-nine people were killed
and over 200 injured today in an explosion at a Hong Kong-funded
fireworks factory at Waihai Town, of the city of Jiangmen, in
south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The blast, which occurred at around 8 a.m., also leveled a two-
story building which covers an area of 3,000 sq m, according to
witnesses.
</P>
