<HEADLINE> Chinese Defence Minister Meets Laotian Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua)-- Chinese Defence Minister Chi
Haotian met here today with Duang Chai, chief of the general staff
of the Lao People's Army and his party.
</P>
<P>
Reviewing the development of Sino-Laotian friendship, Chi, also
vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission and a State
Councilor, said he was deeply impressed by the friendship between
the two peoples and their armed forces during his visit to the
Laos in 1993.
</P>
<P>
He said he is satisfied with the current development of Sino-
Laotian ties and China is willing to make further efforts to
consolidate and develop the Sino-Laotian good-neighborly and
friendly relations in the new century.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of the two governments and armed forces have maintained
frequent visits, Chi noted, adding that these visits have deepened
the mutual understanding, trust, and friendship between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Duang Chai said the Laotian and Chinese peoples have long
supported each other.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese people and armed forces have provided the Laos
valuable assistance, which demonstrates the profound friendship
between the two countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
Duang Chai said he believes the friendly cooperation between
the two countries and their armed forces will continue to grow.
</P>
<P>
</P>
