<HEADLINE> Chinese and Laotian Military Leaders Held Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua)-- Fu Quanyou, chief of the general
staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army, held talks with
Duang Chai, chief of the general staff of the Laotian People's
Army here today.
</P>
<P>
Fu, also a member of the Central Military Commission, said
China and the Laos, two neighboring countries, are trustworthy
friends.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese government and armed forces attach great
importance to the development of the good-neighborly and friendly
cooperative relations with the Laos and are willing to work with
the Laotian people and armed forces to push forward such relations.
</P>
<P>
On the Taiwan issue, Fu said the Taiwan new leader has always
declined to clearly recognize the "One-China" principle, adding
that evasion of the "One-China" principle will lead to nowhere.
</P>
<P>
"We have to listen to his words and watch his deeds at the same
time," Fu said.
</P>
<P>
Fu also briefed the guests on China's views on current regional
and international situation.
</P>
<P>
Duang Chai said the Laos is happy to see the continuous
development of the traditional friendship between the two
countries and their armed forces.
</P>
<P>
He said the military cooperation between the two sides has been
fruitful and expressed his believe that the friendly cooperation
between the two countries and their armed forces will continue to
grow.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the talks, Fu held a welcome ceremony for Duang Chai.
</P>
