<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Weaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- A shocking trade deficit Friday
pulled the Australian dollar down nearly half a US cent.
</P>
<P>
At the close the currency was still only at 59.83 U.S. cents,
from 60.15 late Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Bureau of Statistics announced that the trade
deficit in May was 1.553 billion Australian dollars from a revised
deficit of 572 million Australian dollars in April.
</P>
<P>
But economists said the 1.553 billion Australian dollar deficit
was not as bad as it looked, and the Australian dollar could
regain its lost ground as early as Monday. 
</P>
