<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed mixed Friday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index gained 3.
12 points to 833.37, the all-share Emas Index edged up 0.19 of a
point to 207.15 while the Industrial Index lost 2.15 points to 1,
444.10 and the Second Board Index declined 1.92 points to 215.19.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 465 to 181 while 133 counters were
unchanged and 208 counters untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's total turnover declined to 140.378 million shares
valued at 566.689 million ringgit (149.12 million U.S. dollars)
from 225.811 million shares worth 721.325 million ringgit (189.82
million dollars) on Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
