<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks End Stronger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Solid gains among blue chips
stocks pushed the Australian stocks Friday much higher.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark S&AMP;P/ASX200 closed up 56.7 points, or 1.74 percent,
to another all time high of 3311.2 points while the all ordinaries
added 52.1 points, or 1.63 per cent, to finish at 3257.6 points.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 1.39 billion shares at a value of 4.64
billion Australian dollars (2.78 billion U.S. dollars), with 1005
rises, 803 falls and 521 steady.
</P>
<P>
News Corp gained 70 Australian cents to 23.00 Australian
dollars. Publishing and Broadcasting added seven cents to 12.87
Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Telstra was the top-traded stock, adding 10.6 cents to 6.87
Australian dollars. Cable &AMP; Wireless Optus bucked the overall
trend, dropping 0.4 of a cent to 4.98 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the banking sector, NAB gained 46.7 cents to 27.898
Australian dollars and Commonwealth added 39 cents to 27.69
Australian dollars. Westpac firmed by 12 cents to 12.02 Australian
dollars and ANZ was seven cents higher to 12.81 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Among resource stocks, BHP gained 44.2 cents to 19.75
Australian dollars and Rio Tinto firmed by 95.1 cents to 27.45
Australian dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
