<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Lower on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) shed 11.74 points to
end at 2,037.97 points in light trading.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume contracted to 261.23 million units
valued at 295.72 million Singapore dollars (171.93 million U.S.
dollars). Losers edged out gainers by 134 to 103 with 309 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
AddvalTech topped the volume list registering a turnover of 69.
80 million units. It was followed by PKTech which had 62.57
million shares traded. Achieva was the next with 41.93 million
counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
UOI led gainers of the day rising up 89 cents to close at 2.50
Singapore dollars. TAC 20 came the second rising 28 cents to
finish at 4.04 U.S. dollars. DBS gained 20 cents to end at 22.20
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Venture headed the descent of the day as it sank 140 cents to
close at 17.60 Singapore dollars. Creative 50 retreated 90 cents
to finish at 41.70 Singapore dollars. PacCent shed 60 cents to end
at 23.60 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers attributed Friday's weak performance to the lack of
market participation and losses on Wall Street which weighed down
local bourse.
</P>
<P>
They noted the losses were led mainly by computer networking
and telecom shares, saying they fell after Ericson, the leader in
wireless network equipment, said industry profits may slow.
</P>
</TEXT>
