<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uganda Remains 17th Poorest in World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Uganda has been ranked 17th
poorest country in the world in human development for the second
successive year, according to a newly published report by the
United Nations Development Program (UNDP) .
</P>
<P>
In regard to incomes, education and life expectancy, Uganda has
improved since last year but not enough to climb to a higher
ranking, the UNDP Resident Representative in Uganda Daouda Toure
said.
</P>
<P>
Uganda was one of the 10 poorest countries in the world before
1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
