<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IOC Says Sydney Ready for Olympic Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The International Olympic
Committee said in Sydney on Friday that Sydney is now ready for
the Summer Olympic Games to open in September.
</P>
<P>
"Sydney is ready for the Olympic Games," IOC executive board
member Jacques Rogge declared at a news conference.
</P>
<P>
"With the exception of Lillehammer... we have never seen such a
level of preparation. This is a benchmark for future Olympic
cities," he said.
</P>
<P>
With 77 days to go, all of Sydney's permanent venues are
complete and have already been tested. The Olympic Village and
media centres are also finished.
</P>
<P>
As to security arrangements, Rogge said: "I'm a child of the
1972 (Munich) Olympics when 11 Israeli athletes were killed so I
can say that the Games will be OK as long as secutrity is not
breached."
</P>
<P>
He added, "If that's assured, nothing really bad can happen."
</P>
</TEXT>
