<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Int'l Seminar on Islam Opens in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 30 (Xinhua) -- An international seminar and
dialogue on "Enhancing the Understanding of Islam for the Media"
opened here Friday to correct the image of Islam which was said to
be wrongly portrayed by the media.
</P>
<P>
Opening the three-day seminar, Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad said "There are among us people who act
deliberately to cause Islam to be reviled by others. The Muslims
are ready to correct that image but we need the cooperation of the
media, particularly the Western media."
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said there is so much misunderstanding in this world,
misunderstanding arising from wrong information or inability to
get the right information and because of this misunderstanding
countries and regions, peoples and races and the followers of
different religions hate each other and very often fight each
other.
</P>
<P>
Correct information about each other can help reduce the
animosity and suspicions and bring the groups together into a
great family of people, humankind, to create a better world for
everyone, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
"There is a golden opportunity for the media to help build a
better, a fairer and more just world. There is a great opportunity
for the media to enrich the world, to enrich everyone everywhere,"
the Malaysian prime minister said.
</P>
<P>
"It is not that the Muslims are asking for the media to be
biased in their favor. All they are asking for is fair reporting,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
The media can do much for creating greater understanding of
Islam and Muslims, he said, adding the Muslims are not inherently
against the West, the Christians or the Jews, they want peace as
much as anybody else.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir expressed his hope that the seminar will help the
media to get a clearer picture of Islam and hopefully to
contribute to the understanding of Islam among them all.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was organized in conjunction with the ongoing 27th
Islamic Conference of Foreign Ministers which concludes later
Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
