<DOCNO> XIE20000630.0151 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Boats Search For Survivors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian Naval vessels and local
fishing boats Friday searched for survivors after a ship carrying
nearly 500 passengers vanished during a violent storm in North
Maluku, according to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The ship, Cahaya Bahari, left Tobelo on Halmahera in North
Maluku province on Wednesday en route to Manado, capital of North
Sulawesi province. The ship sank about 64 kilometers off the North
Sulawesi coast, about 1,365 kilometers northeast of Jakarta, on
Thursday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The reports quoted search and rescue coordinator Ering Musa as
saying that rescuers scoured the waters of North Sulawesi.
</P>
<P>
"Nothing has been found so far. There have been no reports of
survivors clinging to bits of the ship's wooden hull or the boat
itself," he said.
</P>
<P>
The ship was allowed to carry up to 270 passengers. But
officials and witnesses said the ship left Tobelo port packed with
nearly 500, mostly refugees from Duma and Makete who fled their
villages after the areas were ravaged by rioters last week.
</P>
<P>
The violence, which broke weeks of calm, has claimed more than
150 persons.
</P>
<P>
It was the second ferry carrying Maluku refugees to have sunk
since the Masnaiat capsized in a storm in Ambon (capital of Maluku
province) waters in May, resulting in the death of more than 40
passengers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000630.0152 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepal's Ancient City to Restore Historic Look </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Nepal's historic city of Patan
is going to have its traditional look restored soon, according to
the United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural
Organization (UNESCO).
</P>
<P>
The UNESCO along with the Patan Municipality and other
organizations are jointly working for the project, UNESCO officer
Hema Gurung told the press Friday.
</P>
<P>
"Agreements have been signed last week. Now we are working on
the cost and design. The real construction works will start as
soon as the monsoon season ends in September," Gurung said.
</P>
<P>
Under this plan, the roads in Patan city will be stone-paved
and vehicles will not be allowed to ply inside the city, the newly
built houses will have new facades with traditional look and
commercial boards will be removed.
</P>
<P>
The UNESCO is going to provide 9,000 U.S. dollars for the plan
as seed money, while the Patan Municipality and Patan Tourism
Development Organization will also contribute to the project.
</P>
<P>
Patan is an ancient city about 5 km southeast of Kathmandu.
Full of Buddhist monuments and Hindu temples with fine bronze
gateways, guardian deities and wonderful carvings.
</P>
<P>
With the flourishing of commerce and business, the city, known
as the City of Artists, is losing its traditional look and style
if no action is taken to protect it. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000630.0153 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Income Tax Bill to Be Tabled in Nepali Parliament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"We will accommodate the justified suggestions and present the
final draft to the Finance Ministry, which will then be tabled in
the parliament for approval," Vidyadhar Mallik, Director General
of the department, told the press Friday.
</P>
<P>
Mallik said the first draft of the bill has already been
prepared and has proposed a number of tax initiatives with the aim
to bring all types of earnings into tax net.
</P>
<P>
Export earnings, dividend, pension, foreign earnings and
capital gains are the major areas which the government wants to
cover under the new act, he said.
</P>
<P>
The new act also attempts to bring cooperatives running banking
services, political parties, schools, non-governmental
organizations and all other profit-making activities under the tax
net.
</P>
<P>
Besides bringing these new areas into tax net, the new act will
serve as the main document for income tax provisions. Currently,
there are a number of acts that govern income tax provisions and
are contradictory to each other.
</P>
<P>
"After enactment of the act, it will work as the main law and
other laws related to income tax will be automatically nullified,"
Mallik said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
