<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Officials Urged to Fight Corruption </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian heads of
government departments who fail to take action against
subordinates accused of corruption will be held responsible and
disciplined.
</P>
<P>
The local Guardian newspaper quoted Prime Minister Frederick
Sumaye as speaking in parliament in the central town of Dodoma on
Thursday that heads of departments must ensure their spheres of
jurisdiction free from graft.
</P>
<P>
"If heads of departments do not summon and reprimand their
subordinates who are alleged to be corrupt, then they will be held
accountable for the offence," said the premier.
</P>
<P>
Over 2,000 civil servants, including senior officials in
government ministries, have been punished for their involvement in
corruption in the past five years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
