<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Economy Slows Down in 1999-2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to the revised estimates of the Annual National
Income released by Central Statistical Organisation (CSO) Friday,
the upward revision in the Gross Domestic Product (GDP) growth
rate for 1999-2000 was mainly due to the recovery in the
manufacturing and agricultural sectors.
</P>
<P>
The revised growth rate in the manufacturing sector stood at 8.
5 percent during 1999-2000 compared to 7 percent estimated earlier.
In 1998-99, the manufacturing sector had posted a growth rate of 3.
6 percent.
</P>
<P>
The drop in the GDP growth rate in 1999-2000 to 6.4 percent
from 6.8 percent in 1998-1999 was mainly due to the poor
performance in the agricultural sector, where the growth declined
to 1.3 percent from 7.2 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
