<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kala-azar Hits Southern Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 30 (Xinhua) -- One person died and more than 85
were infected by Kala-azar in Sarlahi district in southern Nepal
bordering India, a report said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Many people have fled the district due to the fast spread of
the disease and lack of ample medical assistance since its
outbreak a few days ago, The Kathmandu Post said.
</P>
<P>
"At least 85 cases of Kala-azar have been traced in seven
villages of the district till date, but the actual figure must be
much higher as many have fled the district," Senior Health Officer
Raj Singh was quoted as saying Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The district hospital can not accommodate the increasing number
of patients due to limited facilities and resources. However, the
Public Health Section of the district has been using germicides at
the villages affected to control the epidemic, Singh said.
</P>
<P>
Kala-azar, a virulent infectious malarial disease of oriental
tropics, is one of the common diseases in Nepal that takes a toll
of at least several hundred people every year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
