<HEADLINE> OAU Observer Head Urges All Zimbabweans to Work Together </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Amos Sawyer, who led the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) election observer team, has
called on all Zimbabweans to work together for the development of
the country, The Herald newspaper report Friday.
</P>
<P>
Briefing reporters after a two-hour closed meeting with
Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe here Thursday, Sawyer said the
voting in last weekend's parliamentary elections had been
conducted smoothly, and his team was pleased with the process.
</P>
<P>
"The next task now is to have all people of the country rally
behind an agenda of moving forward. As OAU, our interest goes
beyond elections, to seeing that the country remains stable," he
said.
</P>
<P>
The observer team's report, which has already been compiled but
not yet made public, will be presented to the OAU Secretary
General very soon, said Sawyer, former Liberian President.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the pre-election violence that has been used by
other observers to discredit the election, Sawyer said it was an
"unfortunate development" and reemphasized the need for people to
work together.
</P>
<P>
"People must move forward and try to remedy problems of the
past as they move. They have got to heal the wounds and most
importantly they have to move into the future. " 
</P>
</TEXT>
