<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Lower in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed lower in Tokyo
Friday on profit-taking following their gains during the previous
three days.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange lost 64.85 points, or 0.37
percent, from Thursday's close to end at 17,411.05.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, dropped 3.06 points, or 0.19 percent, to 1,
591.60.
</P>
<P>
After falling to the day's low of 17,305.81 in early trading,
the Nikkei index rebounded, helped by bargain-hunting and Friday's
launch of new investment trusts, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section increased to 872.14 million
shares from Thursday's 828.22 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Trading house Marubeni was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Low- and medium-priced issues drew buying, but high-priced
information and technology issues were weak following Thursday's
downturn on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
Brokerages and nonferrous metal makers faced selling, while the
construction, paper and real estate sectors were higher.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, gainers far exceeded
losers 945 to 319 despite the falls in the Nikkei and TOPIX, while
132 issues closed unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
