<HEADLINE> Ningxia's First Expressway Opens to Traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Yaofu-Yesheng section of the
Shizuishan-Zhongning expressway, the first in northwest China's
Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region, opened to traffic today.
</P>
<P>
Costing 1.54 billion yuan (185 million U.S. dollars), the 83-
kilometer-long section between Yaofu and Yesheng towns was
completed 22 months ahead of schedule.
</P>
<P>
The total length of the expressway connecting Shizuishan City
and Zhongning County is 253 kilometers long, so far the largest
highway project in this Muslim-inhabited region.
</P>
<P>
According to the regional communications bureau, the northern
section and the southern section of the expressway are now under
smooth construction.
</P>
<P>
The region is also speeding up the construction of another
expressway and a second-grade highway.  
</P>
</TEXT>
