<HEADLINE> Huge Buddhist Collection Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The imperial edition of a huge
Buddhist collection has been published by a Beijing publishing
house.
</P>
<P>
The Yongle North Collection, widely regarded as the most
important sutra publication produced by the imperial court of the
Ming Dynasty (1368-1644), is now available to everyone, the "
Wenhui Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
The 200-volume collection has a nationwide circulation of 100
sets, the Shanghai-based newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
As an imperial treasure in the Ming court, the block-print
North Collection was carefully preserved by court officials and
rarely seen by the common people.
</P>
<P>
The Palace Museum has a copy of the precious collection.
</P>
</TEXT>
