<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pudong to Host Flower Exposition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's Pudong New District
will host an international garden and flower exposition between
September 20 and October 20.
</P>
<P>
It will be the largest flower exposition in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Hu Wei, deputy director of the district's Administrative
Committee, said 12 million pots of flower will be displayed at the
Central Park.
</P>
<P>
Visitors will be able to see a kind of hydrophyte introduced
from the Amazon River, whose leaf will be as large as a table
capable of supporting 35 kilograms of goods.
</P>
<P>
Some 300 kinds of flowers, grass and rocks will also be on
display, he said.
</P>
<P>
Canada and 14 other countries will participate in the Expo. The
"Montreal Garden" is under construction in the Central Park.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-two Chinese cities including Guangzhou, Nanjing and
Nanning will attend the exposition. Hong Kong and Macao will have
special exhibition areas.
</P>
<P>
The Central Park occupies 140 hectares and has 200 kinds of
plants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
