<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian PM Returns from European Trip </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Indian Prime Minister Atal
Bihari Vajpayee Friday described the first-ever India-European
Union (EU) summit as a "historic event which symbolized the goal
of India and the EU to build a new strategic partnership based on
common values and aspirations.
</P>
<P>
The Indian leader said at the airport on his return after a
five-day visit to Italy and Portugal that the summit, held with
the EU during the trip, had added a new chapter to Indo-EU
friendship and hoped that such a summit would take place hereafter
on a regular basis.
</P>
<P>
Stating that both sides agreed on the importance of sustaining
a dialogue between their respective civil societies, he said an
Indo-EU roundtable would be established as part of the dialogue.
</P>
<P>
The roundtable will comprise eminent non-official personalities
from both sides and a network of think-tanks.
</P>
<P>
On the economic side, he said, an agreement was reached to
elevate cooperation through enhancement of trade and investment.
The EU agreed to encourage larger flows of foreign direct
investment especially in the in infrastructure sector, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
