<HEADLINE> Argentina Beat Colombia 3-1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Gabriel Batistuta scored two first-
half goals as Argentina beat Colombia 3-1 to keep a perfect record
in South American qualifying for the 2002 World Cup.
</P>
<P>
Batistuta scored on a pass from Claudio Lopez at the 23rd
minute, but Frankie Oviedo of Colombia headed in a free kick to
even the score three minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Batistuta scored again on a header, also from Lopez, in the
44th minute. Hernan Crespo, who replaced Batistuta in the second
half, put the game out of the home team's reach by scoring in the
74th on a pass from Cristian Gonzalez.
</P>
<P>
With the win, Argentina garnered 12 points, seven more than
Colombia.
</P>
