<HEADLINE> Thai PM Message Marks Anniversary of Diplomatic Ties With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Thai Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai
sent a letter of congratulations to Chinese Prime Minister Zhu
Rongji Friday on the eve of the 25th anniversary of the
establishment of diplomatic relations between Thailand and China.
</P>
<P>
"The cordial and friendly relations between our two countries
have strengthened significantly over the past 25 years. Sino-Thai
relations have contributed not only to the prosperity of the
peoples of Thailand and the People's Republic of China, but also
to peace, stability and prosperity in the region," Chuan said in
the message.
</P>
<P>
The successful visit of Chinese President Jiang Zemin to
Thailand last year also "marked another important milestone" in
bilateral relations, helping bring the two peoples even closer,
said the prime minister.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the confidence that the official visit by Thai
Queen Sirikit to China in October will further enhance and
strengthen the "happily existing bond of friendship" between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
China and Thailand established diplomatic relations on July 1,
1975. 
</P>
