<HEADLINE> China: Top of the Week (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- January-May profits of State-owned industrial enterprises (
SOE) in China were 4.1 times the amount in the same period of last
year, according to figures that the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
After being offset by losses, profits of the SOEs totaled 69.2
billion yuan (about 8.34 billion U.S. dollars) over the first five
months of the year. In the same time, losses at the money-losing
SOEs decreased by 6.7 percent to 42 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin told visiting Prime Minister
Jose Maria Aznar of Spain that he believes Sino-Spanish relations
will grow more profoundly during the prime minister's new term of
office.
</P>
<P>
-- China said that from 1991 to 1999, its drug-control organs
cracked more than 800,000 drug cases and confiscated 39.67 tons of
heroin, 16.894 tons of opium, 15.079 tons of marijuana and 23.375
tons of methamphetamine in the nationwide campaign in narcotics
control.
</P>
<P>
"China's anti-drug law enforcement organs enforce the laws
strictly and are waging a fierce battle against all drug-related
criminal activities, administering merciless punishment to those
involved in such activities", said a white paper entitled "
Narcotics Control in China" issued by the Information Office of
the State Council.
</P>
<P>
-- More than 1.27 million rural families at the upper reaches
of the Yangtze River have signed contracts with the local
government to convert low-yielding farmland into tree belts and
pastures.
</P>
<P>
-- Short wave telecommunications service in parts of China was
disrupted due to solar motion on June 25, scientists said.
</P>
<P>
The short wave telecommunications connection from Manzhouli in
northeast China to Xinxiang in central China stopped from 8 a.m.
to 12:30 p.m.that day, and the connection from east China's
Qingdao to Xinxiang also came to a halt during the same period.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that "coronal holes" on the solar surface caused
the trouble. Coronal holes, like solar spots, are a form of solar
activity.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese and French scientists have developed the world's
smallest fingerprint identification system.
</P>
<P>
The system, portable and reportedly highly accurate, is the
product of joint efforts of China's advanced fingerprint
identification technology and the IC system of the Bull
Information System Inc. of France.
</P>
<P>
-- President Jiang Zemin hailed the recent completion of the
first working draft of the human genome map in a speech to a
working conference of the ruling Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
Jiang called the Human Genome Project "a great scientific
project in the scientific history of human beings, and vital
importance to the development of life science, medicine and
pharmaceutical study."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000630.0235 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China: Top of the Week (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- China's broad money (currency in circulation plus corporate
and individual savings) amounted to 12.412 trillion yuan by the
end of April, up steadily from the previous month, with savings
continuing to post positive growth.
</P>
<P>
Latest figures from the National Bureau of Statistics (NBS)
show that cash in circulation at the end of April stood at 1.3676
trillion yuan, up from the February figure of 1.3235 trillion yuan.
</P>
<P>
-- China's Ministry of Land and Resources has formulated the
guiding principles for land-use evaluation and approval in the 10
provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities in western China.
</P>
<P>
According to the ministry's Outline on Land Resources
Development and Use for Western Development Program, major
infrastructure projects will be given top priority in land-use
evaluation and approval.
</P>
<P>
-- China is to decorate the broken bridge on the Yalu River,
which forms part of the border between China and the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea (DPRK).
</P>
<P>
Three-colored optical fibers will be used to outline the bridge.
The colors -- yellow, white and blue -- have been selected to
symbolize warmth, purity and peace, respectively. The decorating
work is to be completed in September this year.
</P>
<P>
-- China has scored marked success in fighting urban poverty
and improving environment in the course of urban development and
urbanization, Lou Jiwei, vice minister of finance. China's 668
cities and 1,638 counties have established basic living allowance
systems, Lou said.
</P>
<P>
-- China will readjust prices of oil products for the domestic
market once a month starting from July to readjust its oil pricing
to the global market.
</P>
<P>
The monthly readjustments will help ensure sufficient supplies
of oil and prevent individuals from storing too much oil,
authorities said.
</P>
<P>
The State Development Planning Commission has approved that the
producer prices of gasoline and diesel oil rise by 300 yuan and
100 yuan per ton, respectively, in a directive released on June 1.
</P>
<P>
-- The reform to improve efficiency through downsizing in China
's steel sector has shown good results in a number of iron and
steel companies.
</P>
<P>
Seventy large and medium-sized key iron and steel works now
have a per-capita annual steel output of 122.8 tons, according to
the State Administration of Metallurgical Industry.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
