<HEADLINE> U.S. Releases 20 million Dollars for DPRK Oil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 29 (Xinhua) -- President Bill Clinton Thursday
released 20 million U.S. dollars in energy aid to provide oil to
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK).
</P>
<P>
Under a 1994 agreement, the United States, Japan and South
Korea founded a group to supply the DPRK with two light-water
nuclear reactors and heavy fuel oil in exchange for the DPRK's
promise to freeze its nuclear development program.
</P>
<P>
Clinton said in a certification Thursday that the DPRK appeared
to be living up to its commitment to freeze its nuclear weapons
program.
</P>
<P>
Under U.S. law, Clinton must certify that the DPRK has
terminated its nuclear weapons program before he moves to release
such funds. 
