<HEADLINE> China: Top of the Week (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The following are the major
national news stories Xinhua released over the past week from June
24 to June 30:
</P>
<P>
-- Delegates to the 10th meeting of the Standing Committee of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC)
National Committee have voiced their support for the central
government's strategy to develop western China.
</P>
<P>
The delegates said that a report presented by Vice-Premier Li
Lanqing to the meeting will play a great role in helping the CPPCC
to carry out the strategy. The report focused on the basic
situation of regional development in China and new ideas and
mechanisms for carrying out the strategy.
</P>
<P>
-- The major boat capsizing on upper reaches of the Yangtze
River in southwest China's Sichuan Province, Thursday was a
liability accident, an investigation concluded.
</P>
<P>
Wang Jinxiang, vice governor of Sichuan and also head of an
investigation group for the accident, told Xinhua that overloading,
venturing out in spite of a dense fog, and the captain's improper
operations were the main factors behind the tragedy.
</P>
<P>
The accident also revealed the ineffectiveness of relevant
local departments in supervising safety, Wang added.
</P>
<P>
-- A total of 57,794 items of relics have been discovered so
far in the Sutra Cave at the world-famous Mogao Grottoes in
northwest China's Gansu Province, much more than the widely
reported 50,000, Chinese scholars said. However, the majority of
the relics are now being kept in a dozen foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
Chinese experts have called for the return of the Dunhuang
relics kept by foreign countries to China during the ongoing
series of activities to mark the 100th anniversary of the
discovery of the Sutra Cave.
</P>
<P>
-- A spokesman with the Xinhua News Agency refuted reports by
the Washington Times which tried to discredit the news agency by
making fuss about a normal real estate transaction.
</P>
<P>
He accused the report of "deliberately distorting the fact and
creating rumors with an intention to make trouble."
</P>
<P>
-- China successfully launched a meteorological satellite, the
Fengyun 2, with a Long March 3 carrier rocket at the Xichang
Satellite Launch Center in southwest China's Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
-- China's production of most household electric appliances
grew steadily in the first four months this year, according to the
National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The output of household refrigerators jumped 14 percent year on
year to 4.37 million, and that of color TV sets increased by 5.2
percent to 13.9 million.
</P>
</TEXT>
