<HEADLINE> China to Launch Large Auction Website </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 30 (Xinhua) -- China will open a comprehensive
website for on-line auctions of various commodities on July 7.
</P>
<P>
The website, www.mayala.com, is jointly established by more
than 100 major auction houses in China, led by Hong Kong-based
International Auction Network (China) Co., Ltd..
</P>
<P>
On the opening day, more than a dozen auctions will be held
through the website.
</P>
<P>
Mayala has already established subsidiaries in the Republic of
Korea, Malaysia, Thailand, and Singapore.
</P>
<P>
This year it will mainly concentrate on auctions of corporate
shares, products by small and medium-sized enterprises, and
corporate assets.  
</P>
