<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CDB Approves Loans to Hainan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The China Development Bank (CDB),
China's biggest policy bank, signed a provisional agreement on
lending the country's island province of Hainan 6.34 billion yuan
(763.8 million U.S. dollars) in loans.
</P>
<P>
The fund is expected to support 16 structural and agricultural
projects on the province, today's "China Daily" reports.
</P>
<P>
The package will finance a forestry project to plant 233,300
hectares of fast growing trees in Hainan, with 1.1 billion yuan
acquired in loans from CDB.
</P>
<P>
The forest will be a major provider of raw materials for local
paper industry that boasts an annual production of 600,000 tons,
the report says.
</P>
<P>
Bank officials said that in the past six years, the outstanding
amount of loans by CDB to Hainan has reached 3 billion yuan (361
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
CDB governor Chen Yuan said that the bank will continue to lend
to the area with a view to improving the overall financial
services and helping develop the regional economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
