<HEADLINE> Injury Sidelines U.S. Olympic Soccer Goalkeeper </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 29 (Xinhua)-- Goalkeeper Adin Brown of
Colorado Rapids, expected to start for the U.S. Olympic team in
Sydney, will have surgery on Friday on his injured right knee and
is expected to miss 14-21 days.
</P>
<P>
"It was uncomfortable, and something I felt had to get done,"
Brown said Thursday. "I thought it was going to go away, but it
wound up getting worse and worse."
</P>
<P>
Club trainer Jay Mellette said Brown will have arthroscopic
surgery to clean out the right meniscus, the second time his right
knee has required this procedure.
</P>
<P>
However, the surgery was not done to accommodate the goalie's
need to be ready when the U.S. Olympic team departs for Sydney in
September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
