<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kafelnikov, Pierce Crashed at Wimbledon Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 29 (Xinhua) -- French Open champion Mary Pierce
and Yevgeny Kafelnikov both joined the unlucky seeds on Thursday
when they were crashed at the Wimbledon tennis championships.
</P>
<P>
Pierce, seeded third, lost in the second round 7-6, 7-6 to
Spain's Magui Serna while men's fifth seed Kafelnikov was beaten
by Sweden's Thomas Johansson 6-1, 7-6, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
There are now just seven seeded players left in both the men's
and women's draws after a disastrous first four days for the sport
's leading players.
</P>
<P>
Defending champions Lindsay Davenport and Pete Sampras narrowly
avoided the carnage.
</P>
<P>
Davenport, seeded second, had to scramble back from 0-3 and a
double break down in the final set to squeeze past Russia's Elena
Likhovtseva 3-6, 6-3, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, injured during a second round match against Karol
Kucera on Wednesday, said he fully expected to play against Justin
Gimelstob in the third round on Friday despite a hospital scan
revealing he had acute tendinitis in his left leg.
</P>
<P>
15th seed Safin of Russia joined his friend Kafelnikov on the
sidelines, losing to Czech Martin Damm 7-5, 7-6, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Safin was handed a warning for ball abuse and flirted with
another after smashing his raquet on the floor. But despite all
his yelling, the 20-year-old lost to the more consistent player.
</P>
<P>
Twelfth seed Pat Rafter made no such mistake. The dual U.S.Open
champion bulldozed fellow Australian Todd Woodbridge 6-3, 6-3, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Fourth seed and French Open champion Gustavo Kuerten crushed
qualifier Justin Bower 6-4, 6-4, 7-5.
</P>
<P>
Eighth seed Tim Henman beat France's Arnaud Clement 6-4, 6-4,6-
4 in a workmanlike performance on Center Court to take his place
in the last 32 in the extremely competitive bottom half of the
draw.
</P>
<P>
In the women's draw, Arantxa Sanchez-Vicario and Monica Seles
booked their third round spots.
</P>
<P>
Ninth seed Sanchez-Vicario swept aside Rita Grande of Italy 6-3,
6-1 and sixth seed Seles had little trouble beating Els Callens of
Belgium 6-4, 6-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
