<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romanian Team Worth 100 Million U.S. Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The market value of Romania's
national soccer squad is over 100 million U.S. dollars, the local
weekly Capital reported in its latest issue citing experts in such
evaluation.
</P>
<P>
The weekly said that while the clubs offer almost 4 million U.S.
dollars to the veteran internationals, they offer 10 million U.S.
dollars to the younger players.
</P>
<P>
Defender Cristian Chivu registered the biggest market value,
being sold by the Craiova University to Ajax Amsterdam for 3
million U.S. dollars in 1999. Now, after his remarkable play with
the Euro 2000, Chivu's market value increased four times.
</P>
<P>
The best transfer amounts of money go with Chivu - 12 million U.
S. dollars, Adrian Ilie, Cosmin Contra and Constantin Galca - 10
million U.S. dollars each, followed by Viorel Moldovan and Iulian
Filipescu - 7 million U.S. dollars each and Ionel Ganea - 6
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The weekly also read that a qualification campaign for an
international championship costs about 1.7 million U.S. dollars in
Romania.
</P>
<P>
Romanian soccer players received an 80,000 dollar-bonus for the
Euro 2000 qualification, the bonus value decreasing in accordance
with each player.
</P>
<P>
According to the weekly Capital, if Romania were the Euro 2000
winner, each player would have received 180,000 U.S.dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
