<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Agassi, Martin Match Halted Overnight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The match between second seed Andre
Agassi and Todd Martin was halted on Thursday by bad light at
Wimbledon much to Agassi's relief.
</P>
<P>
Agassi, despite leading the second round match 6-4, 2-6, 7-6,
had just been broken in the opening game of the fourth set.
</P>
<P>
After more than two hours of hard-fought rallies, it began to
spit with rain. He called for Wimbledon referee Alan Mills and was
visibly upset when he was sent back on to the chilly center court
to play on.
</P>
<P>
After slipping on the damp grass when running for a forehand,
Agassi got his way and Mills called an end to play at 30-30 on
Martin's serve.
</P>
<P>
An overnight break will do the world of good for Agassi who
looked the less confident of the two Americans, and his trademark
early returns were rarely seen.
</P>
<P>
Play will resume on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
