<HEADLINE> E. China Province Upgrading Traditional Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANTAI, June 30 (Xinhua) -- East China's coastal province of
Shandong plans to use more overseas funds to upgrade its
traditional industries.
</P>
<P>
More advanced equipment and related technologies will also be
introduced from overseas.
</P>
<P>
An official with the provincial government said multinational
corporations are especially encouraged to take part in this
massive upgrading program.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, traditional industries, including
textiles, machinery, and paper making contribute most to the local
economy.
</P>
<P>
Over the past decade, the province has spent more than 200
billion yuan (about 24 billion U.S. dollars) on technological
transformation in these industries.
</P>
<P>
About 20,000 new products have been developed, which have
contributed 16 percent to the province's total industrial output.
</P>
