<HEADLINE> New Plans for Improve Domestic Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- China has revealed new plans to
improve domestic tourism with the aim of stimulating the
development of the tourist industry and related industries during
the coming holidays.
</P>
<P>
The coming National Day will be another week-long holiday from
October 1-7. The General Office of the State Council has had this
announced three months in advance to make sure there is enough
time for preparing the vast increase of tourists, today's "China
Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
It also published a document on how to further develop tourism
and solve the problems caused by holidays with the assistance of
nine ministries, including the China National Tourism
Administration (CNTA), the State Development Planning Commission
and the State Economic and Trade Commission.
</P>
<P>
The document ordered relevant government departments to
guarantee the safety of transportation and try their best to make
tourists' holidays as successful as possible.
</P>
<P>
The departments of railways, communications and civil aviation
are required to map out transportation programs and prepare
vehicles and airplanes for emergency use.
</P>
<P>
Tourism administrations will open hotlines to handle consumers'
complaints and protect their legislative rights and interest.
</P>
<P>
The Statistics Bureau and CNTA will set up a statistics and
forecast system that enables tourist to access for information via
the media. Measures will be taken to alleviate the undersupply of
hotels and inns.  
</P>
</TEXT>
