<HEADLINE> Urgent: One Person Reported Dead in Ambush on U.N. Convoy in Sierra Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Sierra Leonean rebels
Friday ambushed a U.N. convoy escorted by Jordanian soldiers in
the West African country, killing one person and injuring at least
four, U.N. officials said here.
</P>
<P>
Officials were still checking on details. Oluyeme Adeniji, the
U.N. special representative for Sierra Leone, confirmed that a
convoy of U.N. vehicles was returning from Kenema, in eastern
Sierra Leone, when there "was an exchange of fire" with rebels
from the Revolutionary United Front (RUF), and "the first reports
talk about some injured."
</P>
<P>
Adeniji, in New York to brief the U.N. Security Council Friday,
told reporters that a helicopter had been dispatched to the area
to evacuate any wounded. 
