<HEADLINE> Canada, Costa Rica to Launch Free Trade Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Canada and Costa Rica will have
their first round of free trade talks in Ottawa from July 11 to 14,
Canadian International Trade Minister Pierre Pettigrew announced
Friday.
</P>
<P>
"We see excellent potential for further developing the trade
relationship between Canada and Costa Rica," Pettigrew said,
adding the Central American country "is a perfect market for our
small and medium-sized enterprises to gain experience in accessing
markets in the region."
</P>
<P>
He also described a free trade deal with Costa Rica, which is
expected to be concluded next spring, as part of Canada's
commitment to "the creation of a Free Trade Area of the Americas
by 2005."
</P>
<P>
Canadian Prime Minister Jean Chretien and Costa Rican President
Miguel Angel Rodriguez agreed last January to explore the
possibility of a free trade agreement between the two countries.
</P>
