<DOCNO> XIE20000630.0297 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Annan Highlights Movement's Role on International Day of Cooperatives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The cooperative movement
can help ensure that the benefits of globalization are shared by
all, Secretary-General Kofi Annan said on Friday, the eve of the
International Day of Cooperatives marked each year on the first
Saturday in July.
</P>
<P>
"Founded on the principles of private initiative,
entrepreneurship and self-employment, underpinned by the values of
democracy, equality and solidarity, the movement can help pave the
way to a more just and inclusive economic order," the Secretary-
General said in his message on the Day.
</P>
<P>
He noted that in many countries, cooperatives have developed
into powerful and prosperous economical entities with extensive
organizational structure.
</P>
<P>
The most successful have grown into large-scale, professionally
run and solidly financed enterprises that operate in full
competition with commercial firms while emphasizing expertise that
enables people to help themselves, he said.
</P>
<P>
Stressing that cooperatives serve as an example to those who
would like to see the private sector get more involved in
development activities, he called for making greater use of the
tools that the cooperative movement offers towards the shared goal
of "a more just, more inclusive and more prosperous world."
</P>
<P>
The International Day of Cooperatives was initially celebrated
on the first Saturday in July 1995, marking the centenary of the
International Cooperative Alliance, an umbrella organization
comprising groups of 100 countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
