<HEADLINE> Papandreou: Greece Favors Deeper EU Integration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Greek Foreign Minister George
Papandreou said Friday that Greece was in favor of a process of
deeper European Union (EU) integration.
</P>
<P>
Speaking during a cabinet meeting chaired by Prime Minister
Costas Simitis, Papandreou said that Greece was in favor of
completing the process of institutional reforms to the EU before
new member states began to join so that the expansion would have
any meaning, the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
<P>
He noted that enhancing the process of EU integration was the
best answer to those who took a phobic attitude to globalization.
</P>
<P>
Greece took a positive view of enhanced cooperation in matters
relating to the economy, internal security and law enforcement,
the minister said, adding that Greece was not opposed to enhanced
cooperation but absolutely rejected abolishing member states' veto
rights.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the need for Greece to take an active role in the
discussions concerning Europe's future in order to secure its
place in the "fast lane" of EU nations having closer cooperation.
</P>
