<HEADLINE> Mercosur Presidents Highlight Relevance of the Bloc </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The presidents said in a joint communique issued at the end of
the bloc's 18th summit meeting that Mercosur is also an effective
instrument to face the growing challenges of the international
system.
</P>
<P>
They underscored in their communique the central role of the
macroeconomic convergence and coordination and the advances
achieved during the meeting about the establishment of budget
goals, of public debt, and of prices jointly agreed on.
</P>
<P>
They agreed on the importance of establishing common
disciplines in the matter of incentives for investments, to the
production and to the intrazone exports, and of preventing the
existence of differential treatments that alter the conditions of
competence in the region.
</P>
<P>
They pointed at the importance of the commitment to jointly
negotiate the agreements of commercial trade with third countries.
They underlined the decision of restarting negotiations with the
Community of Andean Nations and of starting talks with Mexico and
South Africa.
</P>
<P>
The presidents stated in the document their satisfaction for
the progress in the approach of Chile and Bolivia to Mercosur, and
for their speedy admission as full members of the bloc.
