<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks End Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks rose Friday
after a government report said Americans' personal spending rose a
bit in May for the second month in a row, which eased worries
about more hike in interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed up 49.85 at 10,447.85
and the technology heavy Nasdaq composite index rose 88.88 at 3,
966.11.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP; Poor'
s 500 index rose 12.21 at 1,454.60.
</P>
<P>
The technology stocks rallied after the U.S. Commerce
Department reported that Americans' personal spending rose just 0.
2 percent in May for the second month in a row, pushing the nation
's personal saving rate up to its highest level since the start of
the year.
</P>
<P>
The new data indicated that consumers began backing away from
their shopping binge and less spending would ease pressures on
inflation and on interest rates.
</P>
<P>
A big rise in chip sales worldwide also helped to drive the
Nasdaq index higher. The Semiconductor Industry Association said
worldwide chip sales hit an all-time high of 15.8 billion U.S.
dollars in May, up 39.8 percent from 11.3 billion dollars a year
ago.
</P>
<P>
The Dow index bounced back in the final hour of trading to
finish higher from an early falling. The index wavered between the
negative and positive territories in the most hours of session.
</P>
<P>
With Friday's advance, the Dow index finished the first half
with a loss of 9 percent for the year while the Nasdaq index was
down 2.54 percent for the first half of the year.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index rose 0.18 at 642.93 and the Russell 2000 index
of smaller companies rose 4.65 at 517.23. But the American Stock
Exchange index fell 3.45 at 935.89
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a narrow margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,532 up, 1,507 down and 372
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 1.4 billion shares from 1.10 billion
in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
