in aid to help the Colombian government to fight drug-trafficking.
Most of the funds will be used to provide the Colombians with 18
Black Hawk and 42 Huey helicopters and help train and equip
Colombian military and national police battalions.
</P>
<P>
The package also includes about 6.4 billion dollars in spending
for the U.S. military, including 2 billion dollars to replenish
Pentagon accounts drained by peacekeeping operations in Kosovo and
2.9 billion dollars to cover the Pentagon's rising fuel costs and
unpaid military health-care bills.
</P>
<P>
Another 661 million dollars will be spent on repairs and
restoration after recent forest fires ravaged the nuclear
laboratory in Los Alamos, New Mexico, and more than 360 dollars
million will go to assist victims of last year's Hurricane Floyd.
</P>
